uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.expr

Class SQLGroupMapper<O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.AbstractContexed
      • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.expr.SQLGroupMapper<O>
  • Type Parameters:
    O - Type being produced
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contexed, ResultMapper<O>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GeneralMapMapper, RangeSearch.InfoMapper, TableMapper

    public abstract class SQLGroupMapper<O>
extends AbstractContexed
implements ResultMapper<O>
    A base class for ResultMappers that use SQL Group-By queries there are methods to add various select clauses to the target string.
    See Also:
    GroupingSQLValue

                   java.lang.String name)
            throws InvalidKeyException
        add a field both as a clause and as an group by key Note the SQLValue can implement GroupingSQLValue to customise behaviours. Literal constants are not legal in group-by clauses so GroupingSQLValue must be implemented when the SQL representation is a constant.

      • addSQLCount

        public final <T> void addSQLCount(SQLValue<T> expr,
                                  java.lang.String name)
        Add a column counting distinct values. We allow SQLValues so we can count references but we are counting the underlying values the count will be too high if multiple values are mapped to the same result so this should not be used if multiple values map to the same key or the results of multiple queries need to be combined
        Parameters:
        expr -
        name -
